12/05/2011
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Officials from 13 countries meeting in Istanbul signed a convention to combat violence against women Wednesday (May 11th). 
During the Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe meeting, Turkish Foreign Minister and president of the committee Ahmet Davutoglu was the first to sign the document. 
Following him were officials from Austria, Germany, Greece, Iceland, Montenegro, Portugal, Finland, France, Spain, Sweden, Slovakia and Luxembourg. 
The convention urges concrete measures to combat violence against women and state aid to victims. 
(Hurriyet, Haber Turk, Aksam - 11/05/11)
